olive oil
3 clove garlic
½ Onion
1 packet chicken drumsticks
1 sachet Sweet Soy Seasoning
1 packet hoisin sauce
1 tbs soy sauce
1 tsp sesame oil
¾ cup water (for the sauce)
20 g butter
1 packet jasmine rice
1.25 cup water (for the rice)
1 carrot
1 Cucumber
1 packet Mixed Salad Leaves
drizzle vinegar (white  wine or rice wine)
1 packet coriander

• Finely chop garlic. Roughly chop onion (see ingredients).
• Season chicken drumsticks on all sides with salt and pepper.

• In a large frying pan, heat a drizzle of olive oil over high heat. Cook chicken drumsticks, turning, until browned on all sides, 3-4 minutes.
• Add sweet soy seasoning and half the garlic and cook until fragrant, 1 minute.

• Transfer chicken drumsticks (including pan juices!), onion, hoisin sauce, the soy sauce, sesame oil and the water (for the sauce) to slow cooker and set cooking temperature to high.
• Place lid on slow cooker and cook, turning drumsticks each hour, until chicken is tender and the meat is falling off the bone, 4 hours.

TIP: If you don't have a slow cooker, preheat oven to 200°C/180°C fan-forced. Transfer mixture to an ovenproof saucepan, cover with lid (or tightly with foil) and bake until pork is tender, 90 minutes.

• When the slow cooker has 20 minutes remaining, in a medium saucepan, heat the butter with a dash of olive oil over medium heat.
• Cook remaining garlic until fragrant, 1-2 minutes. Add jasmine rice, the water (for the rice) and a generous pinch of salt, stir, then bring to the boil.
• Reduce heat to low and cover with a lid.
• Cook for 12 minutes, then remove from heat and keep covered until the rice is tender and the water is absorbed, 10-15 minutes.

TIP: The rice will finish cooking in its own steam so don't peek!

• Meanwhile, using a vegetable peeler, peel carrot into ribbons. Thinly slice cucumber into rounds.
• In a large bowl, combine carrot, cucumber, mixed salad leaves and a drizzle of vinegar and olive oil. Season to taste.

• Divide garlic rice between bowls. Top with hoisin chicken and carrot salad.
• Tear over coriander. Enjoy!